{{Notability|date=July 2010}}
'''Lillian Y. Lim''' is a former [[San Diego]] [[Superior Court]] [[judge]] who retired in 2007. She was the first [[Filipina]] judge in the [[United States]].{{Fact|date=June 2009}}  

Lim was appointed a [[municipal court]] judge by Gov. [[George Deukmejian]] in 1986 and became a Superior Court judge in 1998.<ref>[http://www.signonsandiego.com/news/metro/20070802-0636-1bo2court.html Superior Court judge retires after 22 years]</ref>  She previously worked as a deputy attorney general for the state Department of Justice for nine years, part of which she spent working in the [[Medi-Cal]] fraud unit. 

Lim received her Bachelor of Arts degree in Political Science from [[Brown University]] in Rhode Island and her [[Juris Doctorate]] degree from the [[San Diego]] campus of [[Western State University College of Law]] named the [[Thomas Jefferson School of Law]].<ref>[http://www.foothillsbar.org/newsletters/Feb2002.htm Foothills Bar Association Newsletter, February 2002, "Judges Corner," page 3]</ref>  

